e than books, they are the lifeThe very heart and core of ages past,The reason why men lived and worked and died,The essence and quintessence of their lives.\n\n- Amy\n|\nYou don’t have to like someone, but you have to treat them as you wish to be treated.\n\n- Roy T. Bennett, The Light in the Heart\n|\nFind the beauty in situations where it is not obvious, and you will create voluminous joy in your life.\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, Joyful Living: 101 Ways to Transform Your Spirit and Revitalize Your Life\n|\nIn the liquid amber within the ivory porcelain, the initiated may touch the sweet reticence of Confucius, the piquancy of Laotse, and the ethereal aroma of Sakyamuni himself.\n\n- Kakuzō Okakura, The Book of Tea\n|\nSo write your story as it needs to be written. Write it honestly, and tell it as best you can. I'm not sure that there are any other rules. Not ones that matter.\n\n- Neil\n|\nJoy is all around me, and I celebrate it all.\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, Joyful Living: 101 Ways to Transform Your Spirit and Revitalize Your Life\n|\nYou are the actor, director, producer, and scriptwriter of the play called ‘Your Life’ and you can change the play anytime.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nTo invest your life, you must invest your time and make sure it doesn’t just melt away like Salvador Dali’s melting clock.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nTime doesn’t really ‘march on’. It tends to tip-toe. There’s no parade. No stomping of boots to alert you to its passing. One day, you turn around and it is gone.\n\n- Heather\n|\nLife doesn't imitate art, it imitates bad television.\n\n- Woody\n|\nThe world keeps happening, in accordance with its rules; it's up to us to make sense of it and give it value.\n\n- Sean\n|\nHe died that day because his body had served its purpose. His soul had done what it came to do, learned what it came to learn, and then was free to leave.\n\n- Garth Stein, The Art of Racing in the Rain\n|\nEach coil has the earthquake which created it, as every death has the life that gave birth to it.\n\n- Sorin Cerin, Wisdom Collection: The Book of Wisdom"